        {
          "id": "ch8-m01-p02",
          "title": "Traits vs attributes + identity proofing",
          "content_blocks": [
            {
              "type": "explain",
              "text": "People mix up **traits** and **attributes**. Think: traits are inherent-ish (biometric pattern, age range), attributes are assigned/recorded (employee ID, role, department). **Identity proofing** is the process of verifying a real-world identity before issuing credentials—this is where you reduce fake accounts at the door."
            }
          ],
          "checks": [
            {
              "type": "single_choice",
              "prompt": "Which activity is an example of identity proofing?",
