        {
          "id": "ch8-m02-p02",
          "title": "Authentication vs authorization",
          "content_blocks": [
            {
              "type": "explain",
              "text": "A classic exam trap: **authentication (AuthN)** ≠ **authorization (AuthZ)**. AuthN is proving identity (password, MFA, certificate). AuthZ is the permission decision after identity is known (RBAC/ABAC rules, ACLs). If you remember one thing: you can be authenticated and still be denied authorization."
            }
          ],
