          "title": "Provisioning and deprovisioning",
          "content_blocks": [
            {
              "type": "explain",
              "text": "**Provisioning** is creating access when needed; **deprovisioning** is removing it fast when it’s no longer needed (termination, role change). Delays create 'ghost access'—one of the most common real-world causes of breaches."
            }
