        {
          "id": "ch8-m08-p02",
          "title": "Single sign-on (SSO) basics",
          "content_blocks": [
            {
              "type": "explain",
              "text": "**SSO** lets a user authenticate once and access multiple services without re-authenticating each time. SSO improves usability and can improve security when paired with strong MFA—but it also means a compromised SSO session is high impact."
            }
          ],
          "checks": [
