          "title": "Federation: identity across organizations",
          "content_blocks": [
            {
              "type": "explain",
              "text": "**Federation** allows identities to be used across security domains (e.g., company uses a cloud app without creating new local accounts). It typically involves an Identity Provider (IdP) and a Service Provider (SP). This is how many modern enterprise SSO setups work."
